QIANG MEI received the M.S. degree from Shanghai Maritime University (SMU), Shanghai, China, in 2013, where he is currently pursuing the Ph.D. degree with the Merchant Marine College, aiming at transportation intelligence. He is a member of Jimei University and the National-Local Joint Engineering Research Center for Marine Navigation Aids Services. His research interests include data mining of AIS and deep learning.
QINYOU HU was born in August 1974. He received the Ph.D. degree in computer software and theory from Fudan University, in 2003. In 2005, he went to the Royal Melbourne University of Technology, Australia, for half a year to conduct a postdoctoral research. He is currently a Professor with Shanghai Maritime University, the Assistant Dean of the School of Commerce and Shipping, the Director of the Department of Navigation, the Director of the Maritime Intelligent Information Processing in Shanghai Key Subject Vehicle Application Engineering Leader, the International Editorial Board of the Journal of Gdynia Maritime University, Poland, and a Journal Reviewer of International Journal on Marine Navigation and Safety of Sea Transportation.

